Dashboard split (1/2): shared state object + lib layer + personas panel

First increment of the per-feature module split (esbuild build pipeline
landed previously). Behavior-preserving — same code, reorganized.

- lib/state.js: shared mutable state object (currentPanel, allProjects,
  currentDetailProject, projectPollTimer, chatWaiting, idleTasksCache, …).
  ES modules can't reassign imported bindings, so cross-module mutable state
  moves to state.X; all references in main.js rewritten.
- lib/api.js: api/apiRaw/authHeaders/authUrl + the injected auth-token
  placeholder. lib/ui.js: showToast. lib/format.js: esc/formatBytes/
  formatDate/avatarColor/initials.
- panels/personas.js: first panel extracted (self-contained, lib-only deps).
- main.js imports the above; 2677 -> ~2390 lines.

Remaining panels (chat, library, idle-tasks, settings, insights,
projects, home, hq, nav, status, theme) tracked in docs/TODO.md — done
incrementally with a Mercury visual check as the acceptance gate, since a
missed cross-panel import is a runtime break esbuild can't catch.

Verified: build clean (token placeholder preserved, no dup symbols);
npm test green (29 unit + API + smoke incl. dashboard-serves-with-token).
